    <h3 style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; color: #00000081;"><p>I’m finally starting to explore the quieter corners of my mind — the parts I ignored or couldn’t hear when my life was louder, messier, and moving too fast. For so long, my youth felt like a blur of distractions and survival, and I didn’t realize how many opportunities were sitting right in front of me the whole time.
    <br><br>
    Now that I’m older, I’m learning to slow down and actually listen to myself. I’m noticing instincts I used to brush off, ideas I never gave space to, and paths I didn’t think I was ready for. It feels like I’m uncovering pieces of myself that were always there, just buried under the chaos.
    <br><br>
    I’m not trying to become a different person — I’m trying to understand the person I’ve always been. Every day I’m picking up something I once missed, giving myself permission to grow, and finally stepping into the opportunities I used to overlook.</p></h3>
